id: pm-miqm
title: "Complete the SDK extension-invoke testing surface: runRegisteredHookForTest + override invoke helpers"
description: "Finish the package-author 'invoke' verb. runRegisteredCommandForTest (pm-owm0) lets authors fire a registered command handler and assert behavior, but the OTHER runtime surfaces an extension can register still have only assert* helpers (registration), no supported way to INVOKE them and observe behavior. Authors must hand-build contexts and reach for the internal runtime runners. This completes the command-pipeline invoke surface: (1) runRegisteredHookForTest(hooks, {kind, context}) fires a registered lifecycle hook (before_command|after_command|on_read|on_write|on_index) via the real runtime runner and returns the warnings array ([] = clean); type-safe per-kind context via discriminated union; throws a descriptive error listing kinds-with-registrations when none of that kind exist (a test wiring/typo bug). (2) runRegisteredParserOverrideForTest / runRegisteredPreflightOverrideForTest / runRegisteredCommandOverrideForTest / runRegisteredRendererOverrideForTest / runRegisteredServiceOverrideForTest each wrap the matching runtime runner (runParserOverride/runPreflightOverride/runCommandOverride/runRendererOverride/runServiceOverride), guard that a matching override is registered for the target (command/format/service) so a typo surfaces as a clear error rather than a silent overridden:false, and return the real *OverrideResult verbatim. All helpers async for a uniform await-based API. Export from the public SDK testing barrel, cover to 100%, and document in SDK.md + EXTENSIONS.md. Data-plane invoke (search provider query, vector adapter ops, migration run) is intentionally out of scope here and tracked separately."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:extensions","area:sdk","area:testing",context-management,living-map
